                                                    BRIEF-Lithia announces pricing of senior notes offering
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    4:57 PM ET 07/17/2017
                                                


Lithia Motors Inc (LAD). * Lithia announces pricing of senior notes offering. * Lithia Motors Inc (LAD) - pricing of its previously announced $300 million in aggregate principal amount of its 5.25% senior notes due 2025 Source text for Eikon: Further company coverage:

















                                                    Lithia Announces Pricing of Senior Notes Offering
                                                


                                                    Business Wire – 
                                                    4:47 PM ET 07/17/2017
                                                


Lithia Motors, Inc. (LAD) today announced the pricing of its previously announced $300 million in aggregate principal amount of its 5.25% senior notes due 2025 in a private offering that is exempt from the registration requirements of the Securities Act of 1933, as amended.

















                                                    BRIEF-Lithia announces proposed senior notes offering
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    7:53 AM ET 07/12/2017
                                                


Lithia Motors Inc (LAD). * Lithia Motors Inc (LAD) - ‍intend to offer $300 million in aggregate principal amount of senior notes due 2025 in a private offering​. * Lithia Motors (LAD) - ‍pending final application, net proceeds of offering will be applied to reduce indebtedness​ Source text for Eikon: Further company coverage:

















                                                    BRIEF-Lithia Motors expects Q2 earnings per share $2.05 to $2.11
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    7:25 AM ET 07/12/2017
                                                


Lithia Motors Inc (LAD). * Lithia reports preliminary record second quarter 2017 results. * Expects Q2 adjusted shr $2.20 to $2.26. * Expects Q2 earnings per share $2.05 to $2.11. * Expects Q2 revenue $2.425 billion to $2.475 billion.

















                                                    Lithia Reports Preliminary Record Second Quarter 2017 Results
                                                


                                                    Business Wire – 
                                                    7:15 AM ET 07/12/2017
                                                


Schedules Second Quarter 2017 Conference Call Lithia Motors, Inc. (LAD) today reported that based on preliminary results, second quarter 2017 net income is estimated to be in the range of $51.5 million to $53.0 million, or $2.05 to $2.11 per diluted share.

















                                                    Lithia Announces Proposed Senior Notes Offering
                                                


                                                    Business Wire – 
                                                    7:14 AM ET 07/12/2017
                                                


Lithia Motors, Inc. (LAD) today announced that we intend to offer, subject to market and other conditions, $300 million in aggregate principal amount of senior notes due 2025 in a private offering that is exempt from the registration requirements of the Securities Act of 1933, as amended.

















                                                    BRIEF-Lithia Motors Inc says has acquired Baierl Auto Group
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    2:24 PM ET 05/01/2017
                                                


Lithia Motors Inc (LAD). * Says has acquired Baierl Auto Group in pittsburgh, pennsylvania. * Says on an annualized basis, baierl is estimated to generate $500 million in revenue and $0.15 in earnings per share Source text for Eikon: Further company coverage:

















                                                    Lithia Enters State of Pennsylvania; Baierl Auto Group Joins Lithia
                                                


                                                    Business Wire – 
                                                    2:21 PM ET 05/01/2017
                                                


Lithia Motors, Inc. (LAD) has acquired Baierl Auto Group in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, comprised of Toyota, Honda, Subaru, Ford, Chevrolet, Acura, Kia and Cadillac locations in the affluent retail area of Cranberry Township.

















                                                    Shau-wai Lam stepping down from Lithia Board of Directors
                                                


                                                    Market Wire – 
                                                    6:37 PM ET 02/27/2017
                                                


02/27/17 -- On February 23, 2017, Shau-wai Lam announced that he would be retiring from Lithia's Board of Directors at the completion of his term in April. Mr. Lam will now focus on a new partnership with Lithia that expands the presence of minority dealers in the U.S. Minority consumers represent approximately 30% of new vehicle sales but own only six percent of auto dealerships.

















                                                    Lithia Reports Record Fourth Quarter and Full Year 2016 Results
                                                


                                                    Market Wire – 
                                                    7:00 AM ET 02/15/2017
                                                


02/15/17 -- Lithia Motors, Inc. (LAD) today reported the highest fourth quarter and full year revenue and earnings per share in company history. Fourth quarter 2016 net income per diluted share increased 13% to $2.03 from $1.80 for 2015.

















                                                    Lithia Schedules Release of Fourth Quarter and Full Year 2016 Results
                                                


                                                    Market Wire – 
                                                    7:01 AM ET 01/24/2017
                                                


01/24/17 -- Lithia Motors, Inc. (LAD) announced its fourth quarter and full year 2016 earnings will be released before the market opens on Wednesday, February 15, 2017. How to Participate The conference call may be accessed by telephone at 407-8029. About Lithia Lithia Motors, Inc. (LAD) is one of the largest automotive retailers in the United States and among the fastest growing companies in the Fortune 500.












